s an interesting point: the presence of false news – similar to current fake news – in ancient Greek literature, especially in tragedy and historiography when it comes to the use of the derivatives of ἄγγελος.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aGreek literaturexHistory and criticism. 0aPress and journalism in literature. 4aLiteratur Griechisch. 4aNachrichten. 4aTransmission.  aTidings.  alegacy.  atransmission.  aἄγγελος.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2023 Part 1z978311117578208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishz978311099389908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Classical Studies 2022 Englishz978311099291508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Classical Studies 2022z9783110992878oZDB-23-DGD0 cEPUBz97831110229560 cprintz978311102166940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311102237640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783111022376423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783111022376/original  a978-3-11-099291-5  EBOOK PACKAGE Classical Studies 2022 Englishb2022  a978-3-11-099389-9  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishb2022  a978-3-11-117578-2  DG Plus DeG Package 2023 Part 1b2023  aEBA_CL_CL  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_CL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGDb2022  aZDB-23-DGGb2022